{
  "stem": "25651.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not privy to the discussions between Edelstein and the commandant of Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But presumably Edelstein said, I'm not preparing the transports anymore.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I resign.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, Ruth Bondy in her book on Edelstein says that he resigned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Germans said, this is not a resigning position.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You are appointed, and you will do as you're told.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, that's a construction, because we-- we were not privy to it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there are no documents to prove that this is so.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We only know that subsequently, Edelstein-- well, we know what happened afterwards.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Edelstein was in clink, and apparently the rumor went, in Theresienstadt, that there were-- there was a discrepancy of about 30 people.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And no way-- you know, these machinations, which were being done with bodies that were being shunted in and out, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] those machinations didn't make up the numbers.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But it always made a different number, whereas in Auschwitz, the Germans were quite insistent that every day they had to come to the exact number.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was no-- you counted the bodies, and you counted the people, and there was no discrepancy.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And you stood all night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Sometimes you stood all through the night and the next day until you came to the right number, because then they knew there was one escape or whatever.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There were a few in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we came back into Theresienstadt.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The next thing was that the proteczia is changing, because Murmelstein is now Judenalteste.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So, all the Zionist proteczia is disappearing, and all the [NON-ENGLISH] people on the-- on the Jugent-- on the Judenaltesterat are in a transport in September.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And Milos, myself, and my mom are in the transport.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Leo isn't, although he's on the Zionist list.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
